
    OPMRUN is graphical user interface to Flow that has similar functionality to the commercial simulator’s ECLRUN program.
    Target audience are Reservoir Engineers in a production environment. Developers and experienced Linux users will already have compatible work flows.
    Allows editing and management of OPM Flow’s run time parameters. Default parameters are automatically loaded from Flow, and the user can reset the default set either from a parameter or PRT file.
    Allows simulation jobs to be queued and run. Queue can be set to run in NOSIM mode or RUN mode.
    Queues can be edited, saved and loaded.
    Written in Python 3 and tested under Unbuntu-Mate 18.04 TLS. 
